    "comment": "Rationale: Fbxo45 is enriched in synaptic fractions. Fbxo45 immunoreactivity colocalizes with a presynaptic marker, VGlut1, and a postsynaptic marker, PSD-95. Analyses using immunoelectron microscopy revealed expression of Fbxo45 in both pre- and postsynaptic structures of excitatory hippocampal neurons in culture. Experimental description: Fig. 3A/B: immunoblot analysis of Fbxo45 in adult **mice** is shown.\nFig. 3C: \"immunocytochemistry of primary cultured **rat** hippocampal neurons expressing Fbxo45 is shown.\"\nFig. 3D: Immuno-EM on froze brain sections, species not specified explicitly, likely mouse\n\nPersonal communication with the first author on the species of the Fig.3D data:\n\nQ: \"I would like to use your publication in JBC titled \"Fbxo45, a Novel Ubiquitin Ligase, Regulates Synaptic Activity\" for annotation of Fbxo45. As a formality have to ask you on the species of the tissue used for the EM pictures used in Fig. 3D.\"\n\nA: \"Dear Dr. Pim van Nierop,\n\nThank you for asking.\nI'm Hirobumi Tada, first author in JBC paper.\nWe used mouse in the EM study.\n\nSincerely yours,\nHirobumi Tada\"\n\nMouse species was allowed and selected for annotation.",
